      • createComplex

        public static Complex createComplex(java.lang.String number)
                             throws java.text.ParseException
        Creates a complex number from the given string. Accepts strings in forms a + ib, a + bi, ib, i, a.
        Parameters:
        number - string containing information about the number
        Returns:
        returns the produced number
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - thrown if cannot deduce a number from given string

      • createRootedPolynomial

        public static ComplexRootedPolynomial createRootedPolynomial(Complex[] roots)
        Creates a ComplexRootedPolynomial from the given Complex numbers. Each given number is one root. Example: if given an array {a, b} will produce a rooted polynomial of form (z - a)*(z - b). Must give at least one root.
        Parameters:
        roots - roots of the number
        Returns:
        returns the rooted polynomial

      • createPolynomial

        public static ComplexPolynomial createPolynomial(Complex[] factors)
        Creates a ComplexPolynomial from the given Complex factors. Each given number is factor next to the variable the power of it's index. Example: if given array {a, b, c} will produce a polynomial of form a + b*z + c*z^2.
        Parameters:
        factors - factory of the polynomial
        Returns:
        returs the polynomial
